      "content": "it's more than just being tired though. it's like the mask has become the only thing that exists. when i look in the mirror, i don't even recognize the person looking back. it's just a hollow shell performing tasks. it feels so pointless to keep pretending to be a human being when there's no one actually home anymore.",
