      "content": "i hear you, but doctors just want to \"fix\" the shell so i can go back to performing. but if the \"me\" part is already gone... what am i even trying to fix? it feels like i'm just maintaining an empty house. if a person isn't actually \"there,\" does it even matter if the body keeps going through the motions? it just seems so exhausting to carry around a life that doesn't even belong to me anymore.",
